WHEREAS, on this special day, VHSF, honored guests, speakers, and other attendees
will pay homage to two additional events celebrated on June 14, 2025, namely the 250th
anniversary of the U.S. Army and Flag Day; and
WHEREAS, we are most grateful to VHSF and the Tennessee chapters of the
Daughters of the American Revolution and the National Society United States Daughters of
1812 for their commitment to honoring GSMNP veterans on this day and every day; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we recognize and
commemorate Honor Our Great Smoky Mountain Veterans Day on June 14, 2025, and honor
the military service of Great Smoky Mountains National Park veterans from all conflicts.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
